am·bu·la·to·ry, adjective
Pronunciation: am-by-l-tOr-E 
1 : of, relating to, or adapted to walking <ambulatory exercise>

2 a : able to walk about and not bedridden <an ambulatory patient> 
  b : performed on or involving an ambulatory patient or an outpatient <an ambulatory electrocardiogram> 
    <ambulatory medical care> 

am·bu·la·to·ri·ly /am-by-l-tOr-lE, adverb